orted and inadequately addressed by limited and fragmented interventions” – UNFPA. Photo: Anna Koblanck/IRIN</caption><start_percent_x>0</start_percent_x><start_percent_y>0</start_percent_y><start_percent_scale>100</start_percent_scale><end_percent_x>0</end_percent_x><end_percent_y>0</end_percent_y><end_percent_scale>100</end_percent_scale></slide><slide><timing>8106</timing><file>05.jpg</file><caption>Female genital mutilation is widespread in the east; nationally there is a high degree of misinformation about sexually transmitted infections, including HIV. Photo: Anna Koblanck/IRIN</caption><start_percent_x>0</start_percent_x><start_percent_y>0</start_percent_y><start_percent_scale>100</start_percent_scale><end_percent_x>0</end_percent_x><end_percent_y>0</end_percent_y><end_percent_scale>100</end_percent_scale></slide><slide><timing>10178</timing><file>06.jpg</file><caption>A lack of government capacity and weak donor interest must be addressed if AIDS is to be effectively tackled among communities of humanitarian concern. Photo: Anna Koblanck/IRIN</caption><start_percent_x>0</start_percent_x><start_percent_y>0</start_percent_y><start_percent_scale>100</start_percent_scale><end_percent_x>0</end_percent_x><end_percent_y>0</end_percent_y><end_percent_scale>100</end_percent_scale></slide><slide><timing>12644</timing><file>07.jpg</file><caption>AIDS interventions must be culturally appropriate. “AIDS programming such as condom distribution had to be looked at in a different light as it wasn’t working. Camp elders were offended”  - OCHA’s Senior HIV AIDS Advisor, Loretta Hieber Girardet. Photo: Anna Koblanck/IRIN</caption><start_percent_x>0</start_percent_x><start_percent_y>0</start_percent_y><start_percent_scale>100</start_percent_scale><end_percent_x>0</end_percent_x><end_percent_y>0</end_percent_y><end_percent_scale>100</end_percent_scale></slide></slides><meta><item><parameter>version</parameter><value>658</value></item><item><parameter>credits</parameter><valu